ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would absolutely recommend this course for another student.

ENGL 831 gives you a good overview of some key 19thc novels. If you are interested in thinking about character and things, the secondary reading is particularly helpful. But if you are interesting in discussing other aspects of the novels, this class may not be for you -- it stays true to its course topic.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The topic of things in novels was not something I had thought of very much before, and I found those discussions to be the most enlightening.

Like I said, this course wasn't in my particular subfield, but I found it quite illuminating. The analytical tools I've gained here regarding the understanding of character and consciousness I imagine will be quite helpful for me in the future.
